description:
&lt;p&gt;The newly developing Universal Crisis team based at St Georges Park in Morpeth are looking to provide a needs lead service to the population of Northumberland and North Tyneside. We are looking to recruit Band 6 Community Practitioner to work within working age part of the universal crisis team. We are seeking enthusiastic and experienced individuals to join the team and provide an exemplary standard of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides the following functions; urgent triage, assessment for people in crisis, gate keeping of acute inpatient beds, home based treatment, facilitating early discharge from hospital, and the coordination of Section 136 referrals. The service operates 24 hours a day, 365 days per year via shift working. The service is Home Treatment Accreditation Scheme (HTAS) accredited.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will have clinical expertise in assessment, intervention and evaluation in mental health care. The role will involve the psycho-social assessment of people who have presented to acute medical services. They will be required to provide specialist advice regarding mental illness to service users, carers and other practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kathleen Payne - Team Manager - Older Age Pathway, UCT&lt;/p&gt;
